\Title {Memory Bus for Multi-Fragment LLM Workflows: Context Compression, the Coordination Cliff, and Privacy}
\Author {Syed Abdullah\ Hassan}
\Copyright {Copyright \textcopyright \ 2026\ Syed Abdullah\ Hassan.\ Except otherwise noted, the reuse of this document is authorized under a Creative Commons 4.0 International (CC-BY-4.0) license.}
\CopyrightURL {https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/deed.en}
\Subject {Large language models running in multi-step workflows pay for every token they read. Context compression is the natural lever, yet the single-agent prompt-compression literature does not measure whether the compression that preserves question-answering accuracy also preserves the harder property a planner needs: combining information distributed across several fragments into a correct answer. This thesis studies that question on multi-fragment LLM workflows. The evaluation uses either a deterministic regex parser or a single LLM call with all (compressed) fragments visible as the planner; multi-round agent simulation is outside the empirical scope. Four contributions are delivered. A reproducible coordination benchmark of 150 instances across three workload families. An empirical characterisation of the coordination cliff with a compounding-error model that predicts its position from per-round token recall, cross-architecture validated on Qwen-72B and DeepSeek V4 Pro within a calibrated regime. A catalogue of three RAG pipelines showing compress-first is robustly preferred in both storage- and accuracy-bounded regimes. A memory-bus reference implementation and a summary-level inference-disclosure metric. Headline verdicts: question-answering accuracy decorrelates from coordination success; a sharp cliff exists; planner capacity sets the success ceiling, not the cliff position, within the calibrated regime; information density scales the cliff across datasets; and compression measurably reduces protected-fact disclosure. A cliff-aware adaptive wrapper, CAAC, operationalises the compounding-error bound as a runtime back-off.}
\Keywords [en] {context compression\sep large language models\sep coordination cliff\sep multi-fragment workflows\sep memory bus\sep inference disclosure\sep agentic memory\sep retrieval-augmented generation\sep [fi] kontekstin tiivist\"aminen\sep suuret kielimallit\sep koordinaatiojyrk\"anne\sep monifragmenttiset ty\"onkulut\sep muistiv\"ayl\"a\sep p\"a\"attelyilmaisu\sep agenttinen muisti\sep hakuparannettu generointi}
